      "side": 1,
      "message": "Add comment that this has potential to lease 10 tasks, and so we could end up with a deep-ish pipeline. If this becomes an issue we may want to separate lease/ack into it\u0027s own (single) goroutine and then have numGoroutines runner tasks which pull from the lease/ack goroutine. This should have the same throughput, but at the cost of higher code complexity and the benefit of only leasing out a maximum of ~10 tasks on average (instead of 10*numGoroutines).\n\nAlso note that if we change archive to archive the whole prefix instead of per-stream this becomes moot anyway because we only want an archivist to lease one prefix at a time.",
